            <title>[IO-674] InfiniteCircularInputStream is not infinite if its input buffer contains -1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/IO-674</link>
                <project id="12310477" key="IO">Commons IO</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;InfiniteCircularInputStream&lt;/tt&gt; is not infinite if its input buffer contains -1 since that is the end of stream marker.&lt;/p&gt;

